Consider the following minimal example ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=5fd9665e0b90ff589f07af468da21d98)):

```rust
use futures::{Future, future::ok};

fn main() {
    ok(()).then(|_a: Result<(), ()>| {
        std::process::exit(1);
        Ok(()) as Result<(), ()>
    }).wait().unwrap();
}
```

It compiles successfully but warns me that line 6 (`Ok(()) as Result<(), ()>`) is unreachable.  That is correct, because `std::process::exit` is a diverging function.  But when I remove that line, compilation fails with the following error:

```
error[E0277]: the trait bound `(): futures::future::Future` is not satisfied
```

So I am forced to include unreachable code to work around the error.
